The Herald Tadious Manyepo Sports Reporter
Rodwell Dhlakama has been appointed the Ngezi Platinum Stars coach on a substantive basis following his exploits after taking over the team mid-stream. The former Chapungu mentor was hired to replace Netherlands import Erol Akbay on a caretaker basis in the middle of the term. But he turned the team into a force, finishing the season a strong fourth in the league and bagging silver in the Chibuku Super Cup. Ngezi Platinum Stars chief executive Nyasha Kadenge confirmed Dhlakama’s appointment on a permanent basis. More to follow…